<br>
Dobbain Danger Evilsbane<br>
Halfling Berserker Druid 37th Season<br>
Secondary Tank and the 7th <br>
Incarnation of Karana Rainkeeper<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey Dobban! See if its dead!&quot; /em pokes an ice giant with a stick. &quot;ROAR!!!&quot; &quot;Crud.&quot; <p><p><center><br><img src="http://www.accesswave.ca/~falwith/Bios/dobbsig.jpg"<br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uainasie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ainasie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/31/01 6:17:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A rant about people who rant about porting lol.</span><hr size=1> well i personally dont charge for a TP but if they do give me a donation i keep it, as long as im not busy i dont mind at all helping people out, cause i know when i play my alts its really hard to get a TP unless you always have something to give. <p>Ainasie Anglestouch<BR>38th Season<BR>Druidess of the Mist<BR>Mist Walkers<BR><a href=http://www.geocities.com/tegwedar_ainasie/>www.geocities.com/tegwedar_ainasie/</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ureeny2000.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reeny2000</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/1/01 5:47:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A rant about people who rant about porting lol.</span><hr size=1> When I was first able to do group ports I would accept plat or whatever for Ports. Now seldom to never. If I have the time I will port, no donation necessary. I always go out of the way for &quot;naked peeps&quot; those in need of a port for a CR.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uellendilhsilvermist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellendilh Silvermist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/1/01 7:14:18 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~phiphix/nfalogo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A rant about people who rant about porting lol.</span><hr size=1> The question is not if this is profitable or not in the end.<br>
<br>
The question is that there is an agreement that one person is buying someone else's time for his own benefit. If a price is agreed before the service is given, and the price is not paid afterwards, the agreement has been broken.<br>
<br>
This is called theft and people are allowed to be upset if this happens.  <p><p><HR>
