I have a great deal of trouble with those who offer money for a port, then stiff the porter. I have not had this happen to me in ages, as I got tired of it and pretty much have stopped porting people for money.<br>
My biggest gripe is the jerks who see a Druid camping a Mob, or worse yet...do a who all druid and don't pay attention that the druid is in a Plane or Chardok or Seb or on a dragon raid and try to DEMAND a port.<br>
I don't think anyone playing a Druid or a Wizard are paying their $10 per month to be everyone's taxi or TL service.<br>
We are all here to play the same game.<br>
/rant off<br>
Thanks...I feel better now. <p>Lainiea Lilwolf<BR>
Level 57 Druid<BR>
Guild Leader<BR>
Rainmakers of Karana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urhyianne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhyianne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/5/01 3:49:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A rant about people who rant about porting lol.</span><hr size=1> /agree Lainiea<br>
<br>
i dont mind porting when i have the time and am not deep in tells, raids and or grouping... no funding needed... what i don't like is people asking for a port and then taking ages to show up... because friend X has to sell... friend Y still has to log etc.... and at the same time, people you promised to help out with a CR or port to a raid, have to wait due to those inconsiderate persons...  <p>Rhianne Dreamwhisper
Wanderer
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukinare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/7/01 8:00:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A rant about people who rant about porting lol.</span><hr size=1> Rarely do I put my anon/roleplay flag up. I am proud of my class and level, and wish to have it prominantly displayed. As a consiquence, I often get requests to port/buff people. This is something I am prepared for and I do not mind at all. It's a risk I take.<br>
<br>
HOWEVER.....<br>
<br>
I go to Gfay a lot to do tradeskills. I have all my tradeskill mules (three total) parked at the bank.<br>
<br>
[quote]
A_noob_09 tells you: Can I have some buffs please?

You tell A_noob_09: Sorry, I am working on tradeskills now, I don't have the time.

A_noob_09 scowls at you, ready to attack: You are doing tradeskills, and here I sit, needing a port... My time is more important than you doing tradeskills, etc etc.
[/quote]<br>
<br>
Frankly, I am tired of people who assume this. I get it all the time.<br>
<br>
Again, I really don't mind getting asked for ports, buffs etc (I can turn them down when I am busy without feeling bad), but I am tired of the attitude that my tradeskills are less important that PLing/porting a stranger.<br>
