&quot;The quote man knows where the quotes will go. And the quote man knows where the quotes will go. Quote man!&quot; <p><p><center><br><img src="http://www.accesswave.ca/~falwith/Bios/dobbsig.jpg"<br></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ualysterweedgrowwer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alyster Weedgrowwer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/24/01 12:35:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A rant about people who rant about porting lol.</span><hr size=1> I've never had anyone stiff me. Best I got was a Cane of the Tranquil for a port. When I port I do it for donations. Much easier that way, if someone asks me for a port and I have time to port, I don't talk pp or how much. I just port em, if they donate great, if not no biggie. I would say it all evens out in the end. Now as for people bugging me for ports, it's not that difficult to reply "Sorry, I'm not porting right now". If they start bitching /ignore. <br>
<br>
Alyster Weedgrower<br>
54 Wanderer Xev<br>
Sovereign's Might <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaeroblaster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AeroBLASTER</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(12/27/01 9:58:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A n00bs perspective</span><hr size=1> First of all, let me say that I shamelessly type /w druid 29 60 to find a porter.<br>
<br>
That said, I always try to ask as politely as possible, even when I just died on another continent and need my corpse.  If they turn down my request, then that's that, I don't bug them anymore and look for a different porter.  If I have spare money, I always try to donate a few pp.  However, from all the 100pp for a port to [insert location here] shouts, I can imagine the huge profits from porting and can't wait until I get my 29.<br>
<br>
To all you higher level druids:  thank you for serving as Norrath's taxi service - you aren't unappreciated =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=araxx>Araxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/3/02 4:21:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> porting...</span><hr size=1> I also like to help people in need. I also like to tease people who ask me for ports. Like the other day in CS. I had just finished a quad and was selling to one of the Othmirs.<br>
<br>
Player: Can you port?<br>
Me: I'm a Druid. Yes, I can port.<br>
<br>
Player: Hehe, are you available?<br>
Me: Hmmm, depends where?<br>
<br>
Player: Only WC.<br>
Me: WC huh? Boring place. Ok, where are you.<br>
<br>
Player:At thr Druid Rung.<br>
Player: Ehm, Ring.<br>
Me: ok, meet you on the third rung from the top. Don't fall off!<br>
<br>
And that is how I normally jest when I'm available.<br>
If I can't do a port I explain why. Busy, waiting for someone, on a lengthy run to some place far from a Druid Ring, etc.<br>
<br>
I also like teasing those who pay before the port.<br>
<br>
Player gives you 20pp.<br>
Me: Ok, now is when I run off...<br>
<br>
I normally get a chuckle from that. :)<br>
<br>
I guess it all depends on the person. When I play my alts I have a very hard time getting any SoW or even ports, that is why when I hear someone asking for one I try to help immediately, just to make a difference. :)<br>
<br>
Ciao for now!<br>
<br>
Araxx Darkroot - 53 Wanderer<br>
Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwenutrefoyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twenu Trefoyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>a_treehugger_03</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/3/02 4:50:04 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.triplem.de/Twenu.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: porting...</span><hr size=1> it all depends on how they ask. if someone is polite or tries to roleplay a bit ( i am no roleplayer, but it´s funny to see other people do it), i´ve normally no problem to buff or port them. ( if i´ve time)<br>
but most of the time i get &quot;buff&quot; or &quot;sow&quot; messages ... not even a &quot;plz&quot; ...  <p><BR><b>Twenu Trefoyl</b><BR><i>"hug it, baby !"</i><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujustallyssia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Just Allyssia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ichuu.com/anicat.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(1/3/02 9:19:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/amazonally.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: porting...</span><hr size=1> I never accept cash for ports, not even if they are desparate and shouting 500pp for a port.  Along those same lines tho, I will only port if I'm not in a group that is busy doing xp etc, because usually I'm the main healer and I don't want to slow down my entire group so I can port someone else out.  And now with Luclin and the extra loading times on some people's computer, porting people around takes even longer since I gotta wait for them to zone in before I can disband.  So if I'm avail and not doing anything, I will port most anywhere for free.  But if I'm busy no amount of whining and crying will sway me. ;)<br>
